Saudi Telecom Must Pay Additional Retirement Costs, SPA Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-08-16T06:14:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/saudi-telecom-must-pay-additional-retirement-costs-spa-says.html
Saudi Telecom Co. (STC)  was ordered by the
government to pay any additional costs for its employees’
retirement and social security plans incurred after the
company’s initial share sale, the  Saudi Press Agency  reported
late yesterday, citing a council of ministers meeting.  Saudi Telecom, the kingdom’s largest phone company, sold a
portion of its shares in an initial public offering in 2002.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  